chapter:
Data processing


	In the this chapter we will see how application
	server requests look like.
	We will have a look at the Wolframe
	standard command handler that handles the requests 
	and how it is configured.
	Then we will show how to write programs that declare the functions 
	executing the requests and how you link them to your application.
	Finally we will describe the tools available in Wolframe
	for defect handling and testing.

